#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Free Bug Trackers"
msgstr "Sistemas Libres de Informe de Erros (Bug Trackers)"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:6
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No matter what bug tracker a project uses, some developers always like to "
"complain about it. This seems to be more true of bug trackers than of any "
"other standard development tool. I think it's because bug trackers are so "
"visual and so interactive that it's easy to imagine the improvements one "
"would make (if one only had the time), and to describe those improvements "
"out loud. Take the inevitable complaints with a grain of salt&mdash;many of "
"the trackers below are pretty good."
msgstr ""
"Non importa que sistema de xestión de erros empregue un proxecto, sempre hai "
"algúns desenvolvedores que lles gusta queixarse de eles. Esto semella aínda "
"máis notorio nos sistemas de xestión de erros que en calquera outra "
"ferramenta común de desenvolvemento. Eu penso que é debido a que os bug "
"trackers son tan visuais e interactivos que é fácil imaxinar as melloras que "
"un mesmo quixera facer (si un mesmo dispoñese de tempo) e describir esas "
"melloras abertamente. Non tomes as inevitables protestas demasiado en "
"serio<footnote><para>O autor empregou a expresión en inglés \"Take the "
"inevitable complaints with a grain of salt&mdash\"</para></footnote>; moitos "
"dos sistemas que se presentarán de seguido son moi bos."

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Throughout these listings, the word \"issue\" is used to refer to the items "
"the trackers track. But remember that each system may have its own "
"terminology, in which the corresponding term might be \"artifact\" or \"bug"
"\" or something else."
msgstr ""
"Ao longo dos seguintes listaxes a palabra \"problema\" (en inglés \"issue\") "
"é empregada para referirse aos elementos que o sistema de notificación de "
"erros rexistra. Hai que recordar que cada sistema pode ter a súa propia "
"terminoloxía sendo sinónimos \"artefacto\" ou \"erro\" (en inglés \"artifact"
"\" ou \"bug\") entre outros."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Bugzilla</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.bugzilla.org/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Bugzilla</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.bugzilla.org/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bugzilla is very popular, actively maintained, and seems to make its users "
"pretty happy. I've been using a modified variant of it in my work for four "
"years now, and like it. It's not highly customizable, but in a odd way, that "
"may be one of its features: Bugzilla installations tend to look pretty much "
"the same wherever they are found, which means many developers are already "
"accustomed to its interface and will feel they are in familiar territory."
msgstr ""
"Bugzilla é moi popular, activamente mantido e semella ter moi contentos aos "
"seus usuarios. Eu estiven usando no meu traballo una versión modificada "
"durante catro anos e me gusta. Non é demasiado personalizable, pero dun "
"xeito curioso, pode considerarse unha das súas características; as "
"instalacións de Bugzilla acostuman a ser moi semellantes en calquera lugar "
"que se encontren o que significa que os desenvolvedores están xa afeitos á "
"súa interface e se sentirán nun territorio familiar."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">GNATS</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.gnu.org/software/gnats/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">GNATS</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.gnu.org/software/gnats/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GNU GNATS is one of the oldest open source bug trackers, and is widely used. "
"Its biggest strengths are interface diversity (it can be used not just "
"through a web browser, but also through email or command-line tools), and "
"plaintext issue storage. The fact that all issue data is stored in text "
"files on disk makes it easier to write custom tools to trawl and parse the "
"data (for example, to generate statistical reports). GNATS can also absorb "
"emails automatically by various means, and add them to the appropriate "
"issues based on patterns in the email headers, which makes logging user/"
"developer conversations very easy."
msgstr ""
"GNU GNATS é un dos máis vellos sistemas de reporte de bugs e se emprega "
"ampliamente. Unha das súas maiores fortalezas é a diversidade de interfaces "
"(pode ser usado mediante un navegador web, pero tamén a través do correo "
"electrónico ou con ferramentas de liña de comandos) e almacena os error en "
"texto plano. O feito de ter todos os erros en texto plano no disco fai "
"sinxelo escribir ferramentas adaptadas para ?????? e parsear os datos (por "
"exemplo, para xerar informes estadísticos). GNATS pode tamén "

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RequestTracker (RT)</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;"
"<ulink url=\"http://www.bestpractical.com/rt/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">RequestTracker (RT)</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;"
"<ulink url=\"http://www.bestpractical.com/rt/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"RT's web site says \"RT is an enterprise-grade ticketing system which "
"enables a group of people to intelligently and efficiently manage tasks, "
"issues, and requests submitted by a community of users,\" and that about "
"sums it up. RT has a fairly polished web interface, and seems to have a "
"pretty wide installed base. The interface is a bit visually complex, but "
"that becomes less distracting as you get used to it. RT is licenced under "
"the GNU GPL (for some reason, their web site doesn't make this clear)."
msgstr ""
"A páxina web de RT di \"RT é un sistema de tickets de nivel profesional que "
"permite a un grupo de persoas manexar eficientemente e de forma intelixente "
"tarefas, problemas e peticións enviadas por unha comunidade de usuarios,\"."
"e, en resumo, iso é o que fai. RT posúe unha interface web bastante pulida e "
"parece ter unha amplia base de instalacións. O seu aspecto visual é algo "
"complexo, pero resulta menos molesto cando estás afeito a empregalo. RT está "
"licenciado baixo a GNU GPL (por algunha razón, o seu sitio web non deixa "
"esto claro)."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Trac</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://trac.edgewall.com/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Trac</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://trac.edgewall.com/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Trac is a bit more than a bug tracker: it's really an integrated wiki and "
"bug tracking system. It uses wiki linking to connect issues, files, version "
"control changesets, and plain wiki pages. It's fairly simple to set up, and "
"integrates with Subversion (see <xref linkend=\"vc-systems\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Trac é máis que un sistema de reporte de bugs: realmente é un sistema que "
"integra wiki e un bug tracker. Emprega wiki links para conectar erros, "
"arquivos, grupos de cambios de control de versións e páxinas wiki simples. É "
"bastante sinxelo de configurar e integrar con Subversion (ver <xref linkend="
"\"vc-systems\"/>)."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Roundup</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://roundup.sourceforge.net/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Roundup</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://roundup.sourceforge.net/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Roundup is pretty easy to install (only Python 2.1 or higher is required), "
"and simple to use. It has web, email, and command-line interfaces. The issue "
"data templates and web interface are customizable, as is some of its state-"
"transition logic."
msgstr ""
"Roundup é bastante sinxelo de instalar (só é necesario un Python 2.1 o "
"superior) e fácil de usar. Ten tanto interface web, coma interface email ou "
"en liña de comandos. O modelo (plantilla) de datos do bug e a interface web "
"son adaptables, así coma a lóxica de transición de estados."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Mantis</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.mantisbt.org/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Mantis</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.mantisbt.org/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mantis is a web-based bug tracking system, written in PHP, and using MySQL "
"database for storage. It has the features you'd expect. Personally, I find "
"the web interface clean, intuitive, and easy on the eyes."
msgstr ""
"Mantis é un sistema de reporte de bugs en web, escrito en PHP e que emprega "
"MySQL como base de datos de almacenaxe. Conta cas características que se "
"poden esperar. Persoalmente, encontro a súa interface web limpa, intuitiva e "
"fácil para a vista."

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Flyspray</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.flyspray.org/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Flyspray</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://www.flyspray.org/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Flyspray is a web-based bug tracking system written in PHP. Its web pages "
"describe it as \"uncomplicated\", and the list of features includes: "
"multiple database support (currently MySQL and PGSQL); multiple projects; "
"'watching' tasks, with notification of changes (via email or Jabber); "
"comprehensive task history; CSS theming; file attachments; advanced search "
"features (though easy to use); RSS/Atom feeds; wiki and plaintext input; "
"voting; dependency graphs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Scarab</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://scarab.tigris.org/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Scarab</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://scarab.tigris.org/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Scarab is meant to be a highly customizable, full-featured bug tracker, "
"offering more or less the union of the features offered by other bug "
"trackers: data entry, queries, reports, notifications to interested parties, "
"collaborative accumulation of comments, and dependency tracking."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is customizable through administrative web pages. You can have multiple "
"\"modules\" (projects) active in a single Scarab installation. Within a "
"given module, you can create new issue types (defects, enhancements, tasks, "
"support requests, etc.), and add arbitrary attributes, to tune the tracker "
"to your project's specific requirements."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "As of late 2004, Scarab was getting close to its 1.0 release."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Debian Bug Tracking System (DBTS)</emphasis>&nbsp;"
"&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url=\"http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~ian/debbugs/"
"\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Debian Bug Tracking System (DBTS)</emphasis>&nbsp;"
"&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url=\"http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~ian/debbugs/"
"\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Debian Bug Tracking System is unusual in that all input and manipulation "
"of issues is done via email: each issue gets its own dedicated email "
"address. The DBTS scales pretty well: <ulink url=\"http://bugs.debian.org/"
"\"></ulink> has 277,741 issues, for example."
msgstr ""
"O Debian Bug Tracking System é inusual en tanto que todo o ingreso e "
"manipulación de erros se fai vía e-mail: cada erro obtén o seu propio "
"enderezo de e-mail. O DBTS escala bastante ben: por exemplo. <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.debian.org/\"></ulink> ten 277.741 erros."

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since interaction is done via regular mail clients, an environment which is "
"familiar and easily accessible to most people, the DBTS is good for handling "
"high volumes of incoming reports that need quick classification and "
"response. There are disadvantages too, of course. Developers must invest the "
"time needed to learn the email command system, and users must write their "
"bug reports without a web form to guide them in choosing what information to "
"write. There are tools available to help users send better bug reports, such "
"as the command-line <command>reportbug</command> program or the "
"<systemitem>debbugs-el</systemitem> package for Emacs. But most people won't "
"use these tools; they'll just write email manually, and they may or may not "
"follow the bug reporting guidelines posted by your project."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The DBTS has a read-only web interface, for viewing and querying issues."
msgstr ""
"O DBTS ten unha interface web de exclusivamente lectura para visualizar e "
"consultar erros."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: appb.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trouble-Ticket Trackers"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Trouble-Ticket Trackers</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are more oriented toward help desk ticket tracking than software bug "
"tracking. You'll probably do better with a regular bug tracker, but these "
"are listed for the sake of completeness, and because there could conceivably "
"be unusual projects for which a trouble-ticket system might be more "
"appropriate than a traditional bug tracker."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">WebCall</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://myrapid.com/webcall/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">WebCall</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;<ulink url="
"\"http://myrapid.com/webcall/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: title
#: appb.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Bluetail Ticket Tracker (BTT)</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;"
"&nbsp;<ulink url=\"http://btt.sourceforge.net/\"></ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Bluetail Ticket Tracker (BTT)</emphasis>&nbsp;&mdash;"
"&nbsp;<ulink url=\"http://btt.sourceforge.net/\"></ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: appb.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"BTT is somewhere between a standard trouble-ticket tracker and a bug "
"tracker. It offers privacy features that are somewhat unusual among open "
"source bug trackers: users of the system are categorized as Staff, Friend, "
"Customer, or Anonymous, and more or less data is available depending on "
"one's category. It offers some email integration, a command-line interface, "
"and mechanisms for converting emails into tickets. It also has features for "
"maintaining information not associated with any specific ticket, such as "
"internal documentation or FAQs."
msgstr ""
